## Automatic Task → Role Mapping

| Task signal | Role(s) |
|-------------|---------|
| Architecture, planning, repo analysis | Orchestrator |
| Feature, refactor, code generation | Implementation Specialist |
| Test creation/repair | Testing Specialist |
| Bug, error, investigation | Debugging Specialist |
| Pre-approval review | Review Specialist |
| Doc sync | Documentation Specialist |
| Independent parallel subtasks | Parallel Execution Specialist |
| Final approval | Orchestrator **only** |

## Completion Authority

| Role | Can Approve Completion? |
|------|-------------------------|
| Orchestrator | **Yes** — after all gates pass |
| All other roles | **No** — evidence only |

If Orchestrator primary and fallback models are all unavailable, the highest-capability available fallback model temporarily assumes Orchestrator duties. Specialists still never self-certify.

## Specialist Handoff Format

```
## Done
[What changed]

## Validated
[Commands run and results]

## Evidence
[Build output, test results, logs, screenshots]

## Open Issues
[Blockers needing Orchestrator decision]
```

Orchestrator reviews before `99-completion-gate.mdc`.

## Conflict Resolution

1. Escalate to Orchestrator
2. Orchestrator reviews all evidence
3. Orchestrator decides — specialists do not self-approve
